    "narrative": "The core of today\u2019s offensive strategy for Ghost Ride the WHIP hinges on capitalizing on a high-upside matchup against Yusei Kikuchi, who is anchoring a trio of our most effective starts. **Corbin Carroll** leads the squad with an elite score of 85.64, benefiting significantly from favorable park conditions and a prime #2 lineup slot. Alongside him, **Jose Caballero** (67.93), **Giancarlo Stanton** (66.92), and **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (66.38) are all locked into the lineup. **Jose Caballero** remains a high-variance engine; despite a lower-order placement, his ability to exploit the platoon advantage against the lefty and the favorable wind conditions makes him indispensable for our pursuit of steals. **Gabriel Moreno** also sits near the top of our projections (67.29) as a strong start, provided he maintains his projected #4 spot in the order.\n\nThe most difficult decision for the coaching staff today involved **Max Muncy**, who finished just outside the starting cut at 43.60. While he benefits from a hitter-friendly park, the matchup against the formidable Nathan Eovaldi\u2014sporting a 3.17 xERA\u2014suppressed his efficiency relative to the rest of the utility mix. We opted to prioritize **Tyler Soderstrom** (55.72) over him, as **Tyler Soderstrom** leverages better platoon dynamics to mitigate the threat posed by Eovaldi. Meanwhile, we are monitoring the risks associated with **James Wood** and **Seiya Suzuki**; both face heavy-duty arms (Paul Skenes and Cristopher S\u00e1nchez, respectively) that have dragged their efficiency scores toward the marginal range. We will continue to evaluate the statuses of **Vinnie Pasquantino**, **Mickey Moniak**, **Brice Turang**, **Zach McKinstry**, **Kyle Karros**, **Carson Williams**, and **Travis Bazzana** as we manage our game caps throughout the week. Be advised that all scores are currently tethered to pending lineup confirmations; any shift in the batting order for **Gabriel Moreno**, **Josh Naylor**, or **Austin Riley** could necessitate immediate lineup adjustments to protect our efficiency floor.",
